TANZANIA’s Ambassador to India, Anisa Mbega has promised local farmers to expect more market opportunities after avocado growers managed to export their first consignment to the Asian country recently. The diplomat thanked Tanzania Horticultural Association (TAHA) for partnering with Makambako based Avoafrica Ltd to export avocados consignment to India. Upon receiving the consignment at Jawaharlal Nehru Port in Mumbai on Wednesday, Ms Mbega said: “This is a great opportunity for the country and avocado growers for accessing the Indian market.”